methods.awaitTermination:
**Incompatible overloads text - text from the first overload:**

Blocks until all tasks have completed execution after a shutdown request, or the timeout occurs, whichever
 happens first.

*Overload 1*  
  :return: (boolean) true if this executor terminated and false if the timeout elapsed before termination
  
*Overload 2*  
  :param timeout: (long) - the maximum time to wait
  :param unit: (java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit) - the time unit of the timeout argument
  :return: (boolean) true if this executor terminated and false if the timeout elapsed before termination
methods.shutdown:
Initiates an orderly shutdown in which previously submitted tasks are executed, but no new tasks will be
 accepted. Invocation has no additional effect if already shut down.
 

 This method does not wait for previously submitted tasks to complete execution. Use awaitTermination to do that.
methods.shutdownAndAwaitTermination:
Shuts down and then awaits termination.

*Overload 1*  
  
  
*Overload 2*  
  :param timeout: (long) - the maximum time to wait
  :param unit: (java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit) - the time unit of the timeout argument
  :return: (boolean) true if this executor terminated and false if the timeout elapsed before termination
methods.terminate: Attempt to terminate the ModelFarm by shutting it down and interrupting all worker threads.
